Hey there! Hmm I would recommend 70/30 or 60/40 for the Herakles. The main thing with pg/vg is pg is thinner than vg which allows atomizers to keep up wi th wicking easier. When you're running a prebuilt coil tank generally 60/40 will be optimal for it. Whereas a rebuildable tank (rta) I would recommend 70 /30.

It's a bit of a misconception that more pg = more flavor. Most flavorings do in fact use PG as their carrier, but regardless of pg/vg ratio we put the sa me amount of flavoring in a recipe. The only time the flavoring changes is if you order extra flavoring. We highly recommend going with the original base  recipe prior to adding more flavoring as the recipe is balanced at the original recipe.
